docs.abstract: The resignation and reports of a drawdown in Afghanistan prompted warnings from within the party that the president’s foreign policy could be leading toward dangerous instability on the global stage.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Hawkish Republican lawmakers, still reeling from President Trump’s decision on Wednesday to yank American forces from Syria, found fresh cause for alarm on Thursday, after Defense Secretary Jim Mattis resigned in protest and reports circulated that the president was preparing to pull thousands of troops out of Afghanistan.

headline.main: Mattis’s Resignation Creates New Cracks Between G.O.P. Lawmakers and Trump
headline.print_headline: Fresh Concerns Divide G.O.P. and the President

docs.abstract: On a valedictory tour, Mr. Ryan is putting a high gloss on a speakership of dubious accomplishment. He fulfilled his tax-cutting dream, but the deficit is soaring.
docs.snippet: On a valedictory tour, Mr. Ryan is putting a high gloss on a speakership of dubious accomplishment. He fulfilled his tax-cutting dream, but the deficit is soaring.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Speaker Paul D. Ryan, the self-styled conservative thought leader who struggled to govern in the era of President Trump, declared on Wednesday that politics in America is “broken,” sounding a parting message of alarm about the outrage-fueled discourse of the day even as his exit from Congress seemed to underscore it.

headline.main: Bidding Congress Farewell, Paul Ryan Laments Nation’s ‘Broken’ Politics
headline.print_headline: Ryan Laments ‘Broken’ Politics That Helped Cut His Speakership Short

docs.abstract: The detentions of three Canadian citizens appear to be retaliation for Canada’s arrest of a top Chinese executive at the behest of the Trump administration.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Chinese government has detained a third Canadian citizen, escalating a diplomatic crisis in which it is pushing the United States to relent on legal pressure against one of China’s leading technology companies.

headline.main: China Holds Third Canadian, Escalating Diplomatic Crisis With the United States
headline.print_headline: China Holds Third Canadian, Escalating Diplomatic Crisis With U.S.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Foreshadowing a likely partisan battle next year, Robert L. Wilkie, the secretary of Veterans Affairs, faced sharp questioning from Democrats on Wednesday over how the department will carry out a new expansion of private-sector medical care for veterans.

headline.main: Congress Grills Head of V.A. Over New Health Care Law
headline.print_headline: Lawmakers Put the V.A. Chief on the Spot

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump said on Thursday that he believes the Saudi journalist Jamal Khashoggi is dead, and he expressed confidence in intelligence reports from multiple sources that strongly suggest a high-level Saudi role in Mr. Khashoggi’s assassination.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — He canceled a trip to a cemetery in France where American soldiers from World War I are buried. He did not go to the observance at Arlington National Cemetery on Veterans Day. He has not visited American troops in Iraq or Afghanistan.
